Definition: inclined to or conducive to companionship with others
not inclined to society or companionship

Definition: not disposed to friendship or friendliness

Definition: easy to like; agreeable

Definition: serving or tending to repel

Definition: lacking self-confidence

Definition: being susceptible to the attitudes, feelings, or circumstances of others

Definition: (of characters in literature or drama) tending to evoke antipathetic feelings
